<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Page 91; Calendar Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
138 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEVER GIVE UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Joselito Paule's Dec. 17 letter, I must say that if the writer gives 
up his dream of becoming a film maker based on one sentence by Steven 
Spielberg, then he never believed in it to begin with. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Paule states that he "can't afford (the) risk" of trying to make films of 
"personal satisfaction" in a competitive industry. But I ask Joselito Paule if 
he can afford the risk of knowing that he sold out on his dream, that he didn't 
even try. This is the stuff of mid-life crises. 
</P>
<P>
I share the same dream, an undying passion to tell a good story, and no band of 
cutthroat businessmen is going to keep me from it. 
</P>
<P>
I am a steadfast idealist who believes that the best life a person can live is 
the one closest to his or her dreams. And I believe Steven Spielberg would 
agree with this. 
</P>
<P>
PERRY J. KING 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
