<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABOUT THE TOP MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If your selection of the best movies is any indication, the 1980s was a 
depressing decade indeed. 
</P>
<P>
The best films in the 1980s emphasized brutal, cold-blooded violence and sexual 
perversion ("Blue Velvet," "Once Upon a Time in America," "Prizzi's Honor"), 
marital turmoil ("War of the Roses," "Shoot the Moon"), drug abuse ("Drugstore 
Cowboy"), child degeneration ("Pixote" -- about a 10-year-old pimp, drug user 
and murderer) and even offered a bleak look at the future ("Brazil," "The Road 
Warrior" and "Blade Runner"). 
</P>
<P>
Hopefully, movies in the 1990s will be a little more uplifting. 
</P>
<P>
