<P>
WHAT WOULD FOOD BE WITHOUT CHEMICALS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read with enormous interest the news in Bruce Horovitz's column on marketing 
("Firm Exercises its Social Consciousness," Dec. 5) that a new "socially 
conscious fast-food company" is introducing "chemical-free food" to the 
marketplace. 
</P>
<P>
Since protein, fats, sugars, nucleic acids, salt and water are all chemicals 
that make up the food that we humans and our pets eat, I think you can 
understand why I am intrigued and excited by the revolutionary idea of 
"chemical-free food." I do hope that you plan to run a feature on this 
scientific breakthrough as soon as possible. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT METZGER 
