<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: HOPES AND IMPEDIMENTS BY CHINUA ACHEBE (DOUBLEDAY: $17.95; 186 
PP.) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Grace Edwards-Yearwood 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Achebe has taken on the formidable task of dismantling, brick by tedious 
brick, some of the carefully constructed myths erected by colonialists during 
their occupation." Grace Edwards-Yearwood 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
