<P>
A Coast Guard cutter reached a sinking Greek freighter 800 miles 
north-northeast of Hawaii and picked up half of the 28 crew members while the 
rest battled to save the ship. "It does not look good, but they're not 
abandoning ship yet. They're still trying," Coast Guard Chief Petty Officer 
Dennis Hubbard said. Three Coast Guardsmen from the cutter Sassafras boarded 
the 620-foot M.V. Bulka of Kingston, St. Vincent, which was on its way to South 
Korea from Los Angeles with a cargo of scrap metal, to help with the pumps that 
the vessel has been using to try to pump water out of its cargo hold. 
