<TEXT>
<P>
A bar-based sports bookmaking ring in Santa Barbara County that may have 
handled $200,000 a week in bets was broken up with the arrests of at least six 
people, authorities said Saturday. A team of state and local officers raided 
three bars and several other businesses and residences in Santa Barbara, 
Carpenteria and Santa Maria as well as Rocklin, near Sacramento. The raids 
concluded a six-week investigation led by the Santa Barbara County Sheriff's 
Department. The raids came after undercover officers made a series of large 
cash bets at the bars and traced the movement of money to other locations. 
