<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is New Year's Day. The following will be closed in observance of the 
holiday: 
</P>
<P>
* All county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
* Schools, including colleges and universities. Public elementary, junior and 
high schools will reopen Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
* County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
* City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
* Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
* City offices will be closed on Monday. City offices in Fullerton and Garden 
Grove will also be closed on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Mail: All post offices will be closed, and mail deposited in mailboxes will be 
picked up according to the posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Trash: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers Monday. 
Trash pickup will be a day late the rest of the week. 
</P>
<P>
Buses: Orange County Transit District buses will run on holiday schedule 
Monday. Call the district at (714) 636-7433 for information. The bus routes 
that will be running are: 29, 41, 43, 44, 47, 49, 50, 51, 53, 54, 55, 57, 60, 
64, 66, 69, 70 and 85. There will be no dial-a-ride or car-pool services 
available on the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
Parks: All city and county parks and recreation facilities will be open their 
regular hours Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
