<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN ONOFRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man, believed to be an undocumented immigrant, was struck by 
several vehicles and killed Friday night at 8:10 as he tried to cross 
Interstate 5 near the San Onofre border checkpoint, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, in his late twenties or early thirties, was the last in a group to 
have crossed the highway heading east, said San Diego Deputy Coroner Cal Vine. 
He was struck by several vehicles and all the drivers involved in the incident 
stopped; none have been charged, California Highway Patrol officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was 5-foot tall, weighed 100 pounds and had black hair, brown eyes 
and a neatly trimmed mustache. 
</P>
<P>
None of the other pedestrians in his group stopped, Vine said. 
</P>
