<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO. 12 REBELS HUNT DOWN RAZORBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anderson Hunt scored 28 points, including five three-point baskets in the 
second half, to lead No. 12-ranked Nevada Las Vegas to a 101-93 victory over 
No. 11 Arkansas. 
</P>
<P>
UNLV (7-2) trailed, 48-44, at halftime, but the Rebels started the second half 
with a 9-2 run on baskets by Greg Anthony, Stacey Augmon and Larry Johnson and 
a three-point basket by Hunt. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels led, 84-75, with six minutes to play after Hunt made four 
three-point baskets during an eight-minute span. 
</P>
<P>
Arkansas guard Todd Day made four three-point baskets that kept the Razorbacks 
(8-2) close until the final minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Anthony scored 20 points for UNLV and Augmon added 19. 
</P>
<P>
"We played a great basketball team today," Arkansas Coach Nolan Richardson 
said. "Definitely that was the most physical football -- I mean basketball -- 
team we've ever played in my career." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA123189-0159 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 155993 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 31, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 9; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
