</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Scott became the first two-time champion of the Fiesta Bowl Mile, beating 
Doug Padilla by one-tenth of a second in the fifth-annual race through the 
streets of downtown Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
Scott, 33, finished in a time of 4:05.6 -- well off his American record in the 
mile of 3:47.69. 
</P>
<P>
Padilla, 33, had broken away from the pack in the elite 10-man field with 450 
yards to go and appeared on his way to being the fifth different winner of the 
event. 
</P>
<P>
But Scott, a two-time Olympian, outkicked Padilla in the final 50 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Scott earned $5,000 for the victory. Padilla received $3,000 and Ireland's Ray 
Flynn earned $1,000 for third place at 4:06.1. 
</P>
<P>
Ireland's Marcus O'Sullivan, the 1987 winner, finished fourth at 4:06.5. 
</P>
<P>
Former Arizona State sprinter Jeff Smith was fifth (4:07.1) followed by 
Canada's Doug Consiglio (4:09.4), former Arizona State track standout Treg 
Scott (4:09.8), defending champion Jeff Atkinson (4:11.4), Canada's Graeme Fell 
(4:12.5) and Charles Marsala (4:16.5) of Bloomington, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
Atkinson, a 1988 Olympian from Manhattan Beach, won last year's race in 
4:05.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
