<P>
BRYAN 3RD IN FIESTA BOWL TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Bryan, 11, of Camarillo finished third in the boys' 12-and-under division 
of the Fiesta Bowl tennis tournament in Tempe, Ariz., on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan, seeded third, lost to Ramin Pajan of Vancouver, B. C., 6-4, 6-3, in the 
semifinals but finished third when Rafael Jordan of Puerto Rico defaulted 
because of a muscle pull. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan's twin, Mike, was eliminated from title contention Friday but finished 
fifth with two victories Saturday. Mike, seeded seventh, defeated Corey Guy of 
San Francisco, 7-6, 6-4, and Jake Graiton of Portland, Ore., 6-2, 6-0. 
</P>
