<HEADLINE>
<P>
AA MEMBERS TO OFFER SOBER SOCIALIZING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of Alcoholics Anonymous are sponsoring their annual "marathon meeting" 
for people who are planning to stay sober this New Year's Eve and may need a 
little support in that quest. 
</P>
<P>
The round-the-clock meeting, at 705 N. Harbor Blvd., began Saturday morning and 
will continue until noon Monday. Members offer fellowship and refreshments for 
those who want to socialize during New Year's but who do not want to celebrate 
with alcohol. 
</P>
<P>
The group usually holds the marathons several times a year during various 
holidays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
