<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN INVITED TO APARTMENT FROM BAR STEALS CAR AFTER BADLY BEATING RESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are looking for a man suspected of severely beating a local resident 
Saturday morning and stealing his car. 
</P>
<P>
Daniel Yakush, 38, who had been beaten in the face and upper torso, was found 
by police and paramedics, who received a 4:08 a.m. call that he had been 
attacked in his apartment in the 21000 block of Brookhurst Avenue, Sgt. William 
Peterson said. 
</P>
<P>
Yakush was taken to Hoag Hospital in Newport Beach where he was treated and 
released, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Yakush told police that he met the unidentified man in a bar earlier in the 
evening and had invited the man, described as tall, blond and his early 30s, to 
his apartment. 
</P>
<P>
"After an argument, (Yakush) was beaten," Peterson said. 
</P>
<P>
The attacker then fled with Yakush's dark blue Toyota Celica, license number 
2LOD702, Peterson. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information about the man or the car is asked to call the 
Huntington Beach Police Department at (714) 536-5951 or (714) 960-8811, 
Peterson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ASSAULTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; AUTOMOBILE THEFTS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA123189-0198 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 156134 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 31, 1989, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
